<H2>
Systems Theory
<A NAME="Systems">
</H2>

<PRE><FONT FACE="Comic Sans MS" SIZE=+1>
"The division of the perceived universe
into parts and wholes is convenient
and may be necessary, but no necessity determines
how it shall be done."

                        -- Gregory Bateson, 1979
                           <U>Mind and Nature: A Necessary Unity</U></FONT><TT>

<A HREF="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0932633498/hip-20" TARGET="Window203"><IMG SRC="HIP/0932633498.01.TZZZZZZZ.jpg" border="0" alt="cover" hspace="3" vspace="3"></A>
<A HREF="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0932633498/hip-20" TARGET="Window204">An Introduction to General Systems Thinking</A> 			Weinberg, Gerald M.	1975, 2001
Dorset House Publishing
353 W. 12th St.
New York, NY 10014
<A HREF="http://www.dorsethouse.com">www.dorsethouse.com</A>
