<H2><A Class="H2" HREF="/research/Single_chip_device_to_provide_real-time_3-D_images_from_inside_the_heart_blood_vessels.asp">Single chip device to provide real-time 3-D images from inside the heart, blood vessels (2/25/2014)</A></H2><P><TABLE BORDER='0'><TR><TD><A HREF="/research/Single_chip_device_to_provide_real-time_3-D_images_from_inside_the_heart_blood_vessels.asp"><IMG SRC="/images/thumbnails/840627551.jpg" BORDER="0" ALT="Single chip device to provide real-time 3-D images from inside the heart, blood vessels"></A></TD><TD VALIGN='TOP'>Researchers have developed the technology for a catheter-based device that would provide forward-looking, real-time, three-dimensional imaging from inside the heart, coronary arteries and peripheral blood vessels. ...> <A HREF="/research/Single_chip_device_to_provide_real-time_3-D_images_from_inside_the_heart_blood_vessels.asp">Full Article</A></TD></TR></TABLE></P><HR><H2><A Class="H2" HREF="/research/Making_nanoelectronics_last_longer_for_medical_devices_cyborgs.asp">Making nanoelectronics last longer for medical devices, 'cyborgs' (2/24/2014)</A></H2><P>The debut of cyborgs who are part human and part machine may be a long way off, but researchers say they now may be getting closer. In a study published in American Chemical Society's journal Nano Letters, they report development of a coating that makes nanoelectronics much more stable in conditions mimicking those in the human body. The advance could also aid in the development of very small implanted medical devices for monitoring health and disease....> <A HREF="/research/Making_nanoelectronics_last_longer_for_medical_devices_cyborgs.asp">Full Article</A></P><HR><H2><A Class="H2" HREF="/research/Metal_in_the_heart_is_non-hazardous_to_health.asp">Metal in the heart is non-hazardous to health (2/23/2014)</A></H2><P><TABLE BORDER='0'><TR><TD><A HREF="/research/Metal_in_the_heart_is_non-hazardous_to_health.asp"><IMG SRC="/images/thumbnails/88720977.jpg" BORDER="0" ALT="Metal in the heart is non-hazardous to health"></A></TD><TD VALIGN='TOP'>Materials Scientists at the University of Jena examine implants made of nickel-titanium alloy in a long-term study: The team led by Professor Rettenmayr and his colleague Dr. Andreas Undisz report in the current issue of the scientific journal 'Acta Biomaterialia' that the release of nickel from wires made of nickel-titanium alloys is very low, also over longer periods of time. ...> <A HREF="/research/Metal_in_the_heart_is_non-hazardous_to_health.asp">Full Article</A></TD></TR></TABLE></P><HR><H2><A Class="H2" HREF="/research/Low-powered_high-speed_head-mounted_display_with_augment_reality_chip.asp">Low-powered, high-speed head-mounted display with augment reality chip (2/22/2014)</A></H2><P><TABLE BORDER='0'><TR><TD><A HREF="/research/Low-powered_high-speed_head-mounted_display_with_augment_reality_chip.asp"><IMG SRC="/images/thumbnails/897909820.jpg" BORDER="0" ALT="Low-powered, high-speed head-mounted display with augment reality chip"></A></TD><TD VALIGN='TOP'>Researchers at KAIST developed K-Glass, a wearable ultra low-powered, high-performance head-mounted display with an augment reality chip. ...> <A HREF="/research/Low-powered_high-speed_head-mounted_display_with_augment_reality_chip.asp">Full Article</A></TD></TR></TABLE></P><HR><H2><A Class="H2" HREF="/research/Computer_arranges_pictures_based_on_their_artistic_aspects.asp">Computer arranges pictures based on their artistic aspects (2/21/2014)</A></H2><P><TABLE BORDER='0'><TR><TD><A HREF="/research/Computer_arranges_pictures_based_on_their_artistic_aspects.asp"><IMG SRC="/images/thumbnails/929272174.jpg" BORDER="0" ALT="Computer arranges pictures based on their artistic aspects"></A></TD><TD VALIGN='TOP'>Until now, it has been a time-consuming process for a program to arrange pictures in a consistent order. It is even more complex to order them on the basis of visual characteristics. Computer scientists from Saarbrcken have developed a system to arrange pictures into a consistent order. It requires no more than a small number of pre-sorted example pictures. Operators of online portals or museums could use this technique, for example, to arrange complex datasets. ...> <A HREF="/research/Computer_arranges_pictures_based_on_their_artistic_aspects.asp">Full Article</A></TD></TR></TABLE></P><HR><H2><A Class="H2" HREF="/research/Builder_bots_ditch_blueprints_for_local_cues.asp">Builder bots ditch blueprints for local cues (2/20/2014)</A></H2><P>Termites inspired researchers to design smart robots. Without the coordinated strategy or detailed communication plan that humans building buildings require, these robots can build complex structures....> <A HREF="/research/Builder_bots_ditch_blueprints_for_local_cues.asp">Full Article</A></P>
