              <h4>Benoit Mandelbrot</h4>

              <p><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Beno%C3%AEt_Mandelbrot">Benoit
              Mandelbrot</a> inventor of fractal geometry died on 14th October. There is
              a fascinating and detailed biographical video interview at <a href=
              "http://www.webofstories.com/play/9596">web of stories</a>. Arthur C.
              Clarke said the Mandelbrot set was the most extraordinary discovery in the
              history of mathematics. The Society adopted his set for it's logo in
              2001.</p>

              <p><a href=
              "http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/obituaries/science-obituaries/8069558/Benoit-Mandelbrot.html">
              Telegraph obituary</a>.</p>
