              <h4>Artificial Life update</h4>

              <p>Prof Kevin Warwick at the <a href=
              "http://www.reading.ac.uk/cybernetics/">Department of Cybernetics</a>
              Reading University <a href=
              "http://www.rdg.ac.uk/about/newsandevents/releases/PR16530.asp">announced
              today</a> his team had used a rat brain preparation to control <a href=
              "http://technology.newscientist.com/channel/tech/mg19926696.100-rise-of-the-ratbrained-robots.html">
              a mobile robot</a>.</p>

              <p>The <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Artificial_life">Artificial
              life</a> paradigm of cybernetics seems alive and well with many new
              automata and <a href="http://dan-ball.jp/en/javagame/dust/">simulation
              environments</a>.</p>

              <p>The list of <a href=
              "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Artificial_life_organizations">Alife
              organizations</a> include the "<a href="http://www.greythumb.org/cms/">Grey
              Thumb Society</a>" which welcomes hobbyists.These are some photographs of a
              recent London based <a href=
              "http://www.facebook.com/album.php?aid=60431&amp;l=91524&amp;id=570496188">chapter
              meeting</a>. This is the <a href="http://www.greythumb.org/blog">Grey Thumb
              blog</a>.</p>
