              <h4>1st Cwarel Isaf Conference March 25th - 26th, 2008- Short Report</h4>

              <p><a href="http://www.malik-mzsg.ch/htm/681/en/Homepage_Portal.htm">Malik
              Management Zentrum St Gallen</a> invited the world's leading management
              cyberneticians to a meeting at their new headquarters in St. Gallen,
              Switzerland. The <a href=
              "http://www.managementkybernetik.com/en/fs_inst.html?/en/inh/institut.html">
              Cwarel Isaf Institute</a> was founded by the late <a href=
              "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stafford_Beer">Stafford Beer</a> (and named
              after his cottage in Wales) and Fredmund Malik to make the life's work of
              Beer available to society, to steward his intellectual property and to
              transfer related knowledge into the benefits of practical applications.</p>

              <p>Malik MZSG discussed and presented their approach to management based in
              Cybernetics. The twelve sessions covered the <a href=
              "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Viable_System_Model">Viable System Model</a>,
              <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syntegrity">Syntegration</a>,
              <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ludwig_von_Bertalanffy#General_System_Theory_.28GST.29">
              General Systems</a> Modelling (particularly the approach of <a href=
              "http://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frederic_Vester">Frederick Vester</a> from
              his "The Art of Interconnected Thinking"), <a href=
              "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bionics">Bionics</a> (supported with a richly
              illustrated book, by Malik staff, "Bionics: The intelligence of creation"
              with many contributions including <a href=
              "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scanning_tunneling_microscope">Scanning
              Tunneling Microscopy</a> Nobelist <a href=
              "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gerd_Binnig">Gerd Binnig</a>), Strategic
              Planning, Innovation and Audit.</p>

              <p>Participants agreed, including many from the <a href=
              "http://www.metaphorum.org">Metaphorum Group</a>, this had been most useful
              and well presented development. The world is now closer to realizing the
              wide applicability and benefits of what, today, we can call the risk based
              evolutionary model of Stafford Beer's Viable System.</p>
              <hr />

