    <td width="663" rowspan="2" valign="top" class="blacktext">
<table width="660" border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0">
        <!--DWLayoutTable-->
        <tr> 
          <td width="638" height="30" valign="top" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" class="blacktext"><!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="mian" -->
           
          
            <table width="649" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
              <!--DWLayoutTable-->
              <tr> 
                <td width="233" valign="top"> <p align="justify" class="blacktext"><img src="images/pp_island_aerial_lores.JPG" width="231" height="154"><br>
                    The 2014 IEEE International Conference on Systems, Man, and Cybernetics will be held at the luxurious Paradise Point Resort & Spa where the average October temperature is 70oF/22oC. Tucked away on gentle Mission Bay in the Heart of San Diego, Paradise Point Resort & Spa features comfortable Balinese style bungalows amidst lush, tropical gardens, tranquil lagoons, wildlife, and one mile of sandy beach next door to SeaWorld. Scattered across a private 44-acre island, youll find plenty of room to roam and relax with five swimming pools, beach bon-fire pits, a marina, five dining venues, an award-winning spa and endless recreation options (<a href="http://smc2014.org/">more</a>).</p>
                  <p align="justify" class="blacktext"><img src="images/pp_lagoon_aerial_lores.JPG" width="231" height="154"><br>
                    SMC 2014 is the annual flagship conference of the IEEE Systems, Man, and Cybernetics Society where researchers and practitioners report on up-to-the-minute innovations and developments, summarize state-of-the-art, and exchange ideas, results, and future trends in all aspects of  systems science and engineering, human-machine systems, and cybernetics. Papers are invited on all technical topics ranging from theoretical results to engineering practice and industrial applications (<a href="http://smc2014.org/">more</a>).</p>
                  <p></p></td>
                <td width="10" rowspan="2" valign="top" class="dots"><!--DWLayoutEmptyCell-->&nbsp;</td>
                <td width="406" valign="top"><p><span class="sectiontitle"><strong><span class="sectionyellow">V</span>ision</strong></span></p>
                  <p align="justify" class="blacktext">The vision of the Systems, 
                    Man, and Cybernetics Society is to be recognized<br>
                    as the world leading society for the advancement of theory 
                    and application<br>
                    in systems science and engineering, human-machine systems, 
                    and cybernetics.</p>
                  <p><span class="sectiontitle"><strong><span class="sectionyellow">M</span>ission</strong></span></p>
                  <p align="justify" class="blacktext">The mission of the Systems, 
                    Man, and Cybernetics Society is to serve the interests of 
                    its members and the community at large by promoting the theory, 
                    practice, and interdisciplinary aspects of systems science 
                    and engineering, human-machine systems, and cybernetics. It 
                    is accomplished through conferences, publications, and other 
                    activities that contribute to the professional needs of its 
                    members. </p>
                  <p><strong><span class="sectiontitle"><span class="sectionyellow">V</span>alues</span></strong></p>
                  <p class="blacktext">The following fundamental values provide 
                    the foundation for all SMC activities:</p>
                  <table width="95%" border="0" class="blacktext">
                    <tr> 
                      <td><strong>Membership</strong>: Maximize the value of being 
                        a member.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr> 
                      <td><strong>Professionalism</strong>: Advance knowledge 
                        and professional development.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr> 
                      <td><strong>Excellence</strong>: Deliver high quality and 
                        relevant services and products.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr> 
                      <td><strong>Integrity</strong>: Act with honesty and fairness. 
                      </td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr> 
                      <td><strong>Collaboration</strong>: Achieve results and 
                        excellence through teamwork.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr> 
                      <td><strong>Communication</strong>: Promote honest and transparent 
                        interactions. </td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr> 
                      <td><strong>Diversity</strong>: Embrace diversity of members 
                        and their ideas. </td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr> 
                      <td><strong>Empowermen</strong>t: Empower volunteers and 
                        value their contributions.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr> 
                      <td><strong>Equality</strong>: Provide equal opportunities 
                        to all members.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr> 
                      <td><strong>Respect</strong>: Practice respectfulness in 
                        all relationships.</td>
                    </tr>
                  </table></td>
              </tr>
              <tr> 
                <td></td>
                <td></td>
              </tr>
