<TR ALIGN="CENTER" VALIGN="TOP">
<TD COLSPAN="3" WIDTH="120" BGCOLOR="CC9900" VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="CENTER"><FONT FACE="Helvetica","Arial","Times" COLOR="FFFFFF"><B>ABOUT ASC EVENTS</B></FONT></TD>

<TD BGCOLOR="FFFFCC">&nbsp;</TD>

<TD COLSPAN="11" WIDTH="440" BGCOLOR="FFFFCC" VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT">
<FONT FACE="Helvetica","Arial","Times" COLOR="000000">
<SMALL>
Historically, the field of cybernetics has relied on conferences and similar events as the context for bringing together people from diverse disciplines who have similar interests.  Cybernetics itself coalesced as a discipline during the 1940's in a series of meetings called the Macy Conferences.
<P>
Continuing this tradition, the American Society for Cybernetics has long emphasized the role of regular gatherings in fostering understanding and the exchange of ideas.
<P>
ASC sponsors conferences and other occasional events to provide the multidisciplinary field of cybernetics a focal venue for such interactions.
<P>
This Webpage provides a summary overview of ASC's most recent conferences as well as a listing of major cybernetics events dating back to the original Macy conferences in the 1940's.
</SMALL>
</FONT>
<BR>
&nbsp;
</TD>
</TR>

<TR ALIGN="CENTER" VALIGN="TOP">
<TD width="120" COLSPAN="3" BGCOLOR="CC9900"><HR></TD>
