<TD COLSPAN="11" WIDTH="440" BGCOLOR="FFFFCC" VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT">
<FONT FACE="Helvetica","Arial","Times" COLOR="000000">
<BR>
<SMALL>
The 2003 ASC Conference was held in Vienna (Austria) in mid-November 2003.  ASC  entered into a collaborative co-sponsorship for two events focusing on the work and the contributions of Heinz von Foerster.
<P>
For more information on this recent conference, visit the <A HREF="http://www.asc-cybernetics.org/2003/index.htm">2003 Conference Information Page</A>.
<P>
</SMALL>
</FONT>
<BR>
&nbsp;
</TD>
</TR>

<TR ALIGN="CENTER" VALIGN="TOP">
<TD width="120" COLSPAN="3" BGCOLOR="CC9900"><HR></TD>
<TD width="480" COLSPAN="12" BGCOLOR="FFFFCC"><HR></TD>
</TR>

<TR ALIGN="CENTER" VALIGN="TOP">
<TD COLSPAN="3" WIDTH="120" BGCOLOR="CC9900" VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="CENTER"><FONT FACE="Helvetica","Arial","Times" COLOR="FFFFFF"><B>2002<BR>Santa Cruz</B></FONT></TD>

<TD BGCOLOR="FFFFCC">&nbsp;</TD>

<TD COLSPAN="11" WIDTH="440" BGCOLOR="FFFFCC" VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT">
<FONT FACE="Helvetica","Arial","Times" COLOR="000000">
<BR>
<SMALL>
ASC's 2002 Conference was held June 13 -16, 2002, at the Baskin Visual Arts Studios and The Music Center, University of California Santa Cruz.
<P>
The theme of the 2002 Conference was:
<P> 
Ecological Understanding II:  Design and Conversation 
<P>
The objective of the conference was to address two questions:
<P>
<UL>
<LI>

What can understanding of conversation bring to an understanding of ecology? 
<BR>
&nbsp;
<BR>
<LI>

What can ecological understanding bring to design? 
</UL>
<P>
For more information, visit the <A HREF="http://www.asc-cybernetics.org/2002/index.htm">2002 Conference Legacy Page</A>.
<P>
The Legacy Page offers archival information on the event, its itinerary, and a set of presentation materials, abstracts, notes, etc., submitted by 2002 Conference presenters for inclusion here on the ASC website. 


</SMALL>
</FONT>
<BR>
&nbsp;
</TD>
</TR>

<TR ALIGN="CENTER" VALIGN="TOP">
<TD width="120" COLSPAN="3" BGCOLOR="CC9900"><HR></TD>
<TD width="480" COLSPAN="12" BGCOLOR="FFFFCC"><HR></TD>
</TR>

<TR ALIGN="CENTER" VALIGN="TOP">
<TD COLSPAN="3" WIDTH="120" BGCOLOR="CC9900" VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="CENTER"><FONT FACE="Helvetica","Arial","Times" COLOR="FFFFFF"><B>2001<BR>Vancouver</B></FONT></TD>

<TD BGCOLOR="FFFFCC">&nbsp;</TD>

<TD COLSPAN="11" WIDTH="440" BGCOLOR="FFFFCC" VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT">
<FONT FACE="Helvetica","Arial","Times" COLOR="000000">
<BR>
<SMALL>
ASC's 2001 Conference was held May 27 - 29, 2001 (with extended activities May 23 - 25) at the University of British Columbia Conference Center in Vancouver.
<P>
The theme of the 2001 Conference was:
<P> 
The Praxis of Cybernetics and the Cybernetics of Praxis 
<P>
In our 2001 conference we explored and discussed the "praxis" of cybernetics, that is, its application in any domain. Equally important, we also explored the cybernetics of praxis, that is, what the awareness of how we do what we do modulates our activity in any domain. This was a conference for the practical and for the visionary. As such we envisioned it as an event of interest for the practical visionary and the reflective practitioner. We could say that we are concerned with the heart and soul of what we do. 
<P>
For more information, visit the <A HREF="http://www.asc-cybernetics.org/2001/index.htm">2001 Conference Legacy Page</A>.
<P>
The Legacy Page offers archival information on the event, its itinerary, abstracts, and an archive of selected papers.
</SMALL>
</FONT>
<BR>
&nbsp;
</TD>
</TR>

