2000 <a href="http://www.isss.org/2000meet/2000toc.htm" target="_blank" class="BodyLink">World Congress of Systems Sciences</a>, July 16-19, Ryerson Polytechnic University, Toronto, Ontario (conference organizer Peter A. Corning, local organizer Helmut Burkhardt). This Congress was co-hosted by over 20 organizations including the ASC. There were plenary sessions each morning, followed by afternoon panel discussions and evening events. The ASC contributed a Plenary talk "Conservation and Change" by Humberto Maturana, a Panel on "Conservation and Change, a Circularity in Ethics and Environment." 
        
